<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1910/522938-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.Melody, a French and international musical channel launched in 2001, is already present in the bouquet of Canal + Africa since a few weeks. According to Bruno Lecluse, the Secom Group CEO, “Vintage music on the continent was not accessible before the arrival of Melody Africa [which is broadcast on DTT in the DRC], where there is a strong demand.”With the opportunity to get both channels through Gorse & Co, this demand should be filled quickly. The general manager of Melody and Melody Africa, Jerome Du Toit, said, “This new partnership will reach a wider audience on the African continent.” The international version of the channel is very popular on the continent, its African version will be welcomed.